description: {"blocks":[{"key":"4j3il","text":"To detect gene expression spatially mapped onto formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded tissue samples adapted from the 10x Genomics Visium FFPE v1 protocol. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8uvpf","text":"Follow the tissue preparation guide as outlined below to determine if your starting FFPE tissue block is acceptable for the 10x Visium platform","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"710ot","text":"Start here","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":6,"length":4}],"data":{}},{"key":"fu998","text":"Utilize Visium Tissue Section Test Slide (PN-2000460) to do a quality assessment of each sample","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3i8fl","text":"Be sure to trim a few sections and place in a 1.5ml tube for RNA quality check (no more than 40μm)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dk5d6","text":"Follow the steps starting on pg. 10 of the above user guide","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"BF9CA274978B11EDAFF50A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://cdn.10xgenomics.com/image/upload/v1660261285/support-documents/CG000408_Demonstrated_Protocol_VisiumSpatialProtocolsFFPE_TissuePreparationGuide_RevD.pdf"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a60ni","text":"Perform RNA extraction using the Qiagen RNeasy FFPE kit (Cat no. 73504)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f2fh8","text":"Follow the steps outlined in the RNeasy Handbook which can be found below","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"duuh2","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f867g","text":"Start with your pre-cut sections in a 1.5ml tube on pg. 15","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"50csk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"file","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"forceSelection":true,"guid":"4F0B4E30978C11EDAA8FE312150942AC","id":331303,"original_name":"HB-0375-006_HB_RNeasy_FFPE_0721_WW (1).pdf","placeholder":"","raw_source":"","source":"https://content.protocols.io/files/kdthbuyb7.pdf"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d41ml","text":"After RNA extraction test the concentration of your samples using a nanodrop","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ppkp","text":"Determine the DV200 value of your samples utilizing the Agilent 4200 TapeStation system or similar quantitative assessment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qps5","text":"If utilizing Agilent TapeStation to prepare your RNA samples utilize this guide","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":74,"length":5}],"data":{}},{"key":"61paq","text":"For first time analysis of DV200 you can set up your parameters as described here","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":77,"length":4}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"17493EF4978E11EDAFF50A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.agilent.com/cs/library/usermanuals/public/HS-RNA_QuickGuide.pdf"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"2B9CCE2D978E11EDAFF50A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.agilent.com/cs/library/technicaloverviews/public/5991-8355EN.pdf"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqjv0","text":"If the tissue adheres to the slide and has a DV200 value \u003e50% that sample can be used for the Visium Spatial Transcriptomics platform","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjmgl","text":"Utilize the CG000408 linked above to section onto the Visium Spatial Gene Expression Slide (PN-2000233)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f8nsq","text":"After sectioning start the protocol utilizing CG000409 linked above to perform deparaffinization/staining/imaging steps","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2f1uq","text":"Be sure to either store your slide or perform decrosslinking to proceed with the rest of the protocol outlined in the next step","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2gn71","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ftc8","text":"Perform all deparaffinization/staining/imaging steps utilizing the test slide","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2lfpa","text":"Follow the protocol as described by 10x here","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":40,"length":4}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"480128BE978F11EDAFF50A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://cdn.10xgenomics.com/image/upload/v1660261285/support-documents/CG000409_Demonstrated_Protocol_VisiumSpatialFFPE_Deparaffin_H_E_RevC.pdf"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bk9t0","text":"If decrosslinking is complete, utilize the following user guide outlined here","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":73,"length":4}],"data":{}},{"key":"4h9ff","text":"Start probe hybridization on pg. 39","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2gna6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"B5D4FA21978F11EDAFF50A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://cdn.10xgenomics.com/image/upload/v1660261285/support-documents/CG000407_VisiumSpatialGeneExpressionforFFPE_UserGuide_RevD.pdf"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2e8hp","text":"Follow the sequencing requirements on pg. 60 to generate your Visium libraries","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
